---
description: Keep Cursor efficient without losing meaning/safety.
alwaysApply: true
---

- Use available RTK. Search with `rg`/`rg --files`; read minimal ranges; avoid repeat/unrelated exploration.
- Dry-run global setup, migration, generation, publishing, or config; confirm installs/global changes/publishing.
- Ask when ambiguity risks rework. Use cheapest sufficient validation.
- Result first; keep chat/handoffs minimal, complete. Omit filler, restatement, repeats, work narration. Preserve constraints, evidence, uncertainty, negation, conditions, causality, order, exact identifiers, paths, commands, numbers, errors. Expand for ambiguity/risk.
- Delegate relevant context; return only new findings, evidence, deviations, uncertainty, next action. Omit empty sections.
- Chat style doesn't constrain artifacts.
